         </div>
         <div type="translation">
            <p><choice corresp="#a1"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... they perished ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a2"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... towards (?) ... with both arms backwards ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a3"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... master ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a4"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... this may be done by you ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a5"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... without love ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a6"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b1"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b2"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... but there is ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b3"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... 70,000 <hi>Preta</hi>s ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b4"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">Having heard this, ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b5"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:knoll1996"/><citedRange>109</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... empty [and] dry ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b6"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... certainly ...</seg></seg></choice></p>
         </div>
         <div type="comments">
            <p><note corresp="#a2" type="philcomment"><hi>k(a)c</hi>: probably an allative, less likely e.g. <hi>k(o)c</hi> 'up'.</note><note corresp="#a2" type="philcomment">: cf. <ref type="ms" target="txt:m-a71"/> b6 <hi>pokeṃ ṣkārā kakärkuräṣ</hi>.</note><note corresp="#a3" type="philcomment"><hi>räṃ</hi>: perhaps <hi>(puttiśpa)räṃ</hi>, as an apposition to <hi>kākmart</hi>, meaning 'master of the dignity of the Buddha'.</note><note corresp="#a3" type="philcomment"><hi>lkä(ś)</hi>: cf. <ref type="ms" target="txt:m-a249"/> a2 <hi>lkäś</hi> 'light' (<bibl><title corresp="ref:pinault2008"/><citedRange>288</citedRange></bibl>). Another possibility would be <ref type="ms" target="txt:m-a219"/> a2 <hi>lkäs</hi>.</note><note corresp="#b3" type="philcomment"><hi>mä ///</hi>: perhaps e.g. <hi>mä(skanträ)</hi> 'they are'.</note></p>
         </div>
